     <part part_index="2" name="The 'Chinese yuan' travel guide" page="0" source="2">
      	<article allWordsNum="182">
            	<![CDATA[
Money can take you to a lot of places, especially China's yuan which may inspire your next great trip. The Renminbi notes are not just good for buying things; they are also ready-made travel guides.
<b><font color='#000000'>* 1 yuan</font></b>
What's on the yuan: One of the famous "Ten Scenes of West Lake (西湖十景)" in Hangzhou, Zhejiang province. The two-meter-high stone pagodas (宝塔) you see on the note are located in the water on the south side of Xiaoying Island.
What to see: Summer is always a great time to go boating on the lake, but autumn is magical. A candle is lit inside each pagoda on the night of the Mid-Autumn Festival. It's quite beautiful.
How to get there: Take a West Lake boat.
<b><font color='#000000'>* 5 yuan</font></b>
What's on the yuan: A beautiful view of Mount Tai (泰山) in the heart of Shandong province.
What to see: A UNESCO World Heritage Site (联合国科教文组织世界遗产景观) since 1987 and a place of religious worship (敬奉) for over 3,000 years.
How to get there: Take a minibus that goes halfway up the mountain, and from there, a cable car (缆车) takes you up to the peak.
        	]]>
            </article>
